\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Regarding devices, a commitment is made to the Bring Your Own Device (BYOD)
 model.
 Faced with a situation of this type and others that may occur, it has been
 seen the need to promote from the center the possibility that students
 have their own device to work from anywhere, which will allow them to alternate
 face-to-face classes with online class.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
During the period of confinement, of the 361 students evaluated, only 10%
 have required that the center give them a device to work from home.
 These students are Vocational students (19 higher, 14 middle and 3 basic),
 since all High School students have their own device, which has facilitated
 online work.
 The fact of requiring a work device has not been a problem in their results,
 since 53% of these students have improved their score, with a positive
 average difference of 0.22 points compared to 0.15 for the rest.
\end_layout

